userPromptTemplate:
Generate a 'Write an Email' task for TOEFL Writing (2026 new format).

Difficulty: {{difficulty}}

Requirements:
- Create a realistic academic/campus scenario requiring an email response
- The scenario should specify: who to write to, the purpose, and any key details to include
- Provide a model answer email (150-200 words)
- Provide a scoring rubric with 3 criteria
- Scenario types: professor office hours request, study group coordination, library resource request, advisor appointment, lab partner communication

Respond with this exact JSON structure:
{
  "scenario": {
    "title": "string — brief scenario title",
    "description": "string — the full scenario description (2-4 sentences)",
    "recipient": "string — who to write to (e.g., 'Professor Chen')",
    "purpose": "string — main purpose of the email",
    "keyPoints": ["string — point 1", "string — point 2", "string — point 3"]
  },
  "modelAnswer": "string — the complete model email response",
  "rubric": [
    {
      "criterion": "Content",
      "description": "string — what good content looks like"
    },
    {
      "criterion": "Organization",
      "description": "string — what good organization looks like"
    },
    {
      "criterion": "Language Use",
      "description": "string — what good language use looks like"
    }
  ]
}
